<TITLE> PM apprises president on first 2 months </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 22 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina made a courtesy call on president Zillur Rahman at Bangabhaban on Sunday, to apprise him of her government's first two months in power. A press release, signed by press secretary to the president Abdul Awal Hawlader, said the prime minister, expressing her deep condolences for the victims of the BDR mutiny, told the president of the various support measures for the families of the slain army officers and other victims. The president praised the prime minister and her government for tackling the crisis with patience and courage. He assured all kinds of cooperation, expressing his satisfaction over the activities of the government. Major general Tareq Ahmed Siddique, adviser to the prime minister, and press secretaries were present during the meeting, the first between Sheikh Hasina and Zillur Rahman since he assumed office as president. b
